article.description: Craig hits 22 as USC Upstate beats ETSU 75-63
article.headline: Craig hits 22 as USC Upstate beats ETSU 75-63
article.linkText: Craig hits 22 as USC Upstate beats ETSU 75-63
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Torrey Craig scored 22 points and pulled down 15 rebounds to lead South Carolina Upstate to a 75-63 win over East Tennessee State Monday night. Craig, who averages 16.9 points per game, has now scored 2,003 career points at USC Upstate (15-11, 8-5 Atlantic Sun Conference). Ricardo Glenn, who leads the conference in rebounding averaging 7.5 a game, pulled down 15 and scored 18 points. Fred Miller added 15 points for the Spartans. ETSU held a 33-31 halftime advantage but Fred Miller made a layup to start the second half as the Spartans went on a 13-0 run to lead 44-33 at the 16:15 mark. The Spartans stretched that to 64-46 with 6:00 remaining. The Buccaneers shot just 24.2 percent from the field in the second half. Jalen Riley had 26 points, Rashawn Rembert added 11 and Lester Wilson had 10 for ETSU (14-12, 7-6).
